<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="192" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,738,1447]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,738,763]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Female: BL= 
<quantity box="[440,535,739,763]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.9" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="9.9">9.9 mm</quantity>
; EW= 
<quantity box="[612,707,738,763]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" pageId="5" pageNumber="192" unit="mm" value="2.6">2.6 mm</quantity>
. Body brownish. Head, pronotum and scape with dense pale yellowish hairs which are relatively long and thin, suberect with bent down tip. Antennae with scape short and thick, 1.80 times as long as wide; relative length of segments from 1st to 6th: 58: 15: 53: 56: 84: 84 (the 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,811,835]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">type</typeStatus>
specimen lacking left apical 5 segments and right 10 segments). Elytra with foveae arranged in regular rows but more or less irregular beside suture and apical area; scales relatively long and thin, suberect and curved, 2.3 times as long as the diameter of each fovea, alternating on rows of foveae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,738,1447]" box="[199,450,954,979]" pageId="5" pageNumber="192">Male: Unknown to us.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
